cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.CC

The paper deals with two-player games on graphs with quantitative objectives, which are classic topics in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problems, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.LO). The introduction of conservative approximations involves the use of algorithms and decision-making, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
